Inverted Full pyramid
Given an integer n as input, print an inverted full pyramid of n rows.
Input Format:
Take input an integer from stdin.
Output Format:
Print the pattern
Example Input:
10
Output:
* * * * * * * * * * 
 * * * * * * * * * 
  * * * * * * * * 
   * * * * * * * 
    * * * * * * 
     * * * * * 
      * * * * 
       * * * 
        * * 
         *
SOLUTION:

//inverted pyramid

#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
    int n;
    scanf("%d",&n);
    for(int i=0;i<n;i++)
    {
        printf("%*s",i,"");
        for(int j=i;j<n;j++)
            printf("* ");
        printf("\n");
    }
    
}
